 188:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****     [..]
 189:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      The compilation define  USE_HAL_XSPI_REGISTER_CALLBACKS when set to 1
 190:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      allows the user to configure dynamically the driver callbacks.
 191:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c **** 
 192:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****     [..]
 193:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      Use function HAL_XSPI_RegisterCallback() to register a user callback,
 194:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      it allows to register following callbacks:
 195:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) ErrorCallback : callback when error occurs.
 196:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) AbortCpltCallback : callback when abort is completed.
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccJ6uCW8.s 			page 5


 197:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) FifoThresholdCallback : callback when the fifo threshold is reached.
 198:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) CmdCpltCallback : callback when a command without data is completed.
 199:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) RxCpltCallback : callback when a reception transfer is completed.
 200:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) TxCpltCallback : callback when a transmission transfer is completed.
 201:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) RxHalfCpltCallback : callback when half of the reception transfer is completed.
 202:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) TxHalfCpltCallback : callback when half of the transmission transfer is completed.
 203:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) StatusMatchCallback : callback when a status match occurs.
 204:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) TimeOutCallback : callback when the timeout perioed expires.
 205:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) MspInitCallback    : XSPI MspInit.
 206:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) MspDeInitCallback  : XSPI MspDeInit.
 207:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****     [..]
 208:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      This function takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle, the Callback ID
 209:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      and a pointer to the user callback function.
 210:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c **** 
 211:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****     [..]
 212:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      Use function HAL_XSPI_UnRegisterCallback() to reset a callback to the default
 213:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      weak (overridden) function. It allows to reset following callbacks:
 214:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) ErrorCallback : callback when error occurs.
 215:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) AbortCpltCallback : callback when abort is completed.
 216:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) FifoThresholdCallback : callback when the fifo threshold is reached.
 217:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) CmdCpltCallback : callback when a command without data is completed.
 218:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) RxCpltCallback : callback when a reception transfer is completed.
 219:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) TxCpltCallback : callback when a transmission transfer is completed.
 220:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) RxHalfCpltCallback : callback when half of the reception transfer is completed.
 221:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) TxHalfCpltCallback : callback when half of the transmission transfer is completed.
 222:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) StatusMatchCallback : callback when a status match occurs.
 223:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) TimeOutCallback : callback when the timeout perioed expires.
 224:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) MspInitCallback    : XSPI MspInit.
 225:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) MspDeInitCallback  : XSPI MspDeInit.
 226:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****     [..]
 227:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      This function takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle and the Callback ID.
 228:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c **** 
 229:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****     [..]
 230:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      By default, after the HAL_XSPI_Init() and if the state is HAL_XSPI_STATE_RESET
 231:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      all callbacks are reset to the corresponding legacy weak (overridden) functions.
 232:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit callbacks that are respectively
 233:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      reset to the legacy weak (overridden) functions in the HAL_XSPI_Init()
 234:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      and HAL_XSPI_DeInit() only when these callbacks are null (not registered beforehand).
 235:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      If not, MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the HAL_XSPI_Init() and HAL_XSPI_DeInit()
 236:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand)
 237:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c **** 
 238:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****     [..]
 239:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in READY state only.
 240:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      Exception done for MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks that can be registered/unregistered
 241:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      in READY or RESET state, thus registered (user) MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used
 242:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      during the Init/DeInit.
 243:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      In that case first register the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 244:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      using HAL_XSPI_RegisterCallback() before calling HAL_XSPI_DeInit()
 245:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      or HAL_XSPI_Init() function.
 246:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c **** 
 247:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****     [..]
 248:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      When The compilation define USE_HAL_XSPI_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or
 249:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      not defined, the callback registering feature is not available
 250:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      and weak (overridden) callbacks are used.
 251:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c **** 
 252:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****   @endverbatim
